The paper discusses the over-smoothing issue in Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) and proposes methods to alleviate it. This topic is closely related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, which suggests that cs.LG and cs.AI are likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the impact of graph topology on the over-smoothing issue, which suggests that cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper includes experiments on graph datasets, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a possible sub-category as well.
